sql:
SELECT impl_name
FROM jcf_implementations
WHERE is_sorted = 1 AND calls_hash_code = 1;

SELECT implementation_type, COUNT(*) as type_count
FROM jcf_implementations
GROUP BY implementation_type;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_sorted_implementations
FROM jcf_implementations
WHERE is_sorted = 1;

SELECT impl_name, description
FROM jcf_implementations
ORDER BY impl_name;

external_knowledge:
JCF implementations refer to the various classes in the Java Collections Framework, such as ArrayList and HashMap; 
A scenario refers to a specific test case or use case for JCF implementations, which may involve different dataset sizes; 
The top performing implementations are those with the lowest average time taken to perform an operation within a scenario.
